265
00:19:44.770 --> 00:19:47.310
- Know what?
- That we were in love.

266
00:19:50.190 --> 00:19:51.140
Love?

267
00:19:53.900 --> 00:19:54.820
Baby,

268
00:19:55.150 --> 00:19:58.350
believe me, you don't want to
go falling in love with a guy like me.

269
00:19:58.530 --> 00:20:01.200
It's too late, Tommy.
I'm crazy about you.

270
00:20:01.450 --> 00:20:03.770
I'm breathing it,
drinking it all in,

271
00:20:04.490 --> 00:20:05.360
aren't you?

272
00:20:08.370 --> 00:20:10.330
I don't know
what I'm drinking,

273
00:20:10.710 --> 00:20:13.000
dollface,
but if this is love...

274
00:20:13.790 --> 00:20:15.070
pour me another glass?

275
00:20:16.130 --> 00:20:18.800
Mr. Carter,
are you trying to be bad at this?

276
00:20:19.510 --> 00:20:21.250
No, just comes naturally.

277
00:20:23.430 --> 00:20:26.050
All right, everybody,
let's go to the end.

278
00:20:31.890 --> 00:20:34.730
Don't even pretend like
you're not going to be great.

279
00:20:34.890 --> 00:20:37.860
- Okay. See you tomorrow.
- See you.

280
00:20:42.150 --> 00:20:43.230
- Hi.
- Hi.

281
00:20:50.530 --> 00:20:52.240
Would it kill you to try?

282
00:20:52.410 --> 00:20:54.870
Yes, and I'm too young to die.

283
00:20:56.000 --> 00:20:58.400
You don't care about classes
or graduating, but you like school...

284
00:20:58.580 --> 00:21:02.090
because you're popular
and you'll never be on top again.

285
00:21:03.250 --> 00:21:04.710
That's thoroughly predictable.

286
00:21:05.380 --> 00:21:07.620
Your act only works on an audience.

287
00:21:40.870 --> 00:21:42.150
Feeling Christian?

288
00:21:42.790 --> 00:21:43.620
Seat belt?

289
00:22:05.770 --> 00:22:07.680
- I forfeit.
- Thank you.

290
00:22:08.850 --> 00:22:09.640
Forty-two.

291
00:22:11.560 --> 00:22:13.390
What do you mean, forty-two?

292
00:22:13.570 --> 00:22:15.940
Forty-two is befriend
somebody I don't like.

293
00:22:19.030 --> 00:22:21.990
It's a to-do list for my life.

294
00:22:22.160 --> 00:22:24.070
What, like
getting a new personality?

295
00:22:24.240 --> 00:22:25.900
Join the Peace Corps,

296
00:22:26.160 --> 00:22:28.490
- make a medical discovery...
- That's ambitious.

297
00:22:28.660 --> 00:22:31.540
be in two places at once,
get a tattoo.

298
00:22:34.250 --> 00:22:35.500
What's number one?

299
00:22:37.800 --> 00:22:38.880
I'd tell you...

300
00:22:39.630 --> 00:22:41.260
but then I'd have to kill you.

301
00:22:58.190 --> 00:23:00.980
- I've come to see if you're ready.
- Take a good look, lady,

302
00:23:01.230 --> 00:23:03.860
because the only thing
I'm ready for is a dirt nap.

303
00:23:04.030 --> 00:23:06.820
Ready to look inside
your heart, Tom Thornton.

304
00:23:06.990 --> 00:23:10.080
You words have been heard,
and not just by me.

305
00:23:11.700 --> 00:23:13.200
When you walked into...

306
00:23:16.000 --> 00:23:19.450
Shit. When you walked out of the rain
and into my club,

307
00:23:19.630 --> 00:23:21.130
that wasn't just a coincidence.

308
00:23:21.290 --> 00:23:23.340
Nothing's coincidence, baby.

309
00:23:23.500 --> 00:23:27.010
You know you're the only one
who can make me sing.

310
00:23:27.670 --> 00:23:30.760
Oh, yeah, Miss Garber! You're gonna
put Eric in all your plays!

311
00:23:31.470 --> 00:23:33.600
- Eric, I'll put you in all my plays!
- Come on, man!

312
00:23:33.760 --> 00:23:34.930
Come on.

313
00:23:35.390 --> 00:23:37.800
I got three weeks to memorize this!

314
00:23:37.980 --> 00:23:40.380
You couldn't pull this off
in three months!

315
00:23:40.560 --> 00:23:42.520
DeNiro couldn't make this work!

316
00:23:42.940 --> 00:23:44.480
- Look, I didn't write it, okay?
- No, but

317
00:23:44.650 --> 00:23:47.060
you'll make a jackass of yourself

318
00:23:47.230 --> 00:23:50.070
in front of the town,
the school, your friends--

319
00:23:50.240 --> 00:23:52.700
I don't have a choice,
so would you help me out, please?

320
00:23:56.240 --> 00:23:57.900
You know
I'm busting on you, right?

321
00:23:58.370 --> 00:24:01.540
I'll be there opening night,
front row,

322
00:24:01.710 --> 00:24:03.040
and you can count on it.

323
00:24:03.790 --> 00:24:05.070
With tomatoes.

324
00:24:06.590 --> 00:24:07.530
Thanks, man.

325
00:24:08.380 --> 00:24:09.080
Landon...

326
00:24:09.920 --> 00:24:12.220
Boys, can you help
with these groceries?

327
00:24:12.510 --> 00:24:13.920
- Yeah.
- No problem.

328
00:24:23.020 --> 00:24:24.050
Jamie.

329
00:24:26.480 --> 00:24:28.940
What do you want, Carter?
I've known you for years.

330
00:24:29.110 --> 00:24:31.650
You're never the first one
to come up and say hello.

331
00:24:33.900 --> 00:24:35.530
I need help with my lines.

332
00:24:37.990 --> 00:24:40.310
Landon Carter's asking me
for help?

333
00:24:40.570 --> 00:24:41.410
Yeah.

334
00:24:42.370 --> 00:24:44.190
Okay, I'll pray for you.

335
00:24:45.910 --> 00:24:47.650
Jamie. No, look...

336
00:24:47.830 --> 00:24:50.790
You've obviously never asked
anyone for help before, right?

337
00:24:52.170 --> 00:24:54.460
A request like yours requires

338
00:24:55.170 --> 00:24:57.410
flattery and groveling.

339
00:24:57.670 --> 00:24:59.170
It can't be all about you.

340
00:24:59.340 --> 00:25:00.970
It has to be for the common good
of everyone.

341
00:25:01.130 --> 00:25:04.500
It is for the common good.
Eddie Zimmerhoff deserves the best.

342
00:25:06.810 --> 00:25:07.720
Please?

343
00:25:08.430 --> 00:25:10.640
Okay. One condition, though.

344
00:25:10.980 --> 00:25:11.840
What's that?

345
00:25:12.730 --> 00:25:15.650
You have to promise
you won't fall in love with me.

346
00:25:19.820 --> 00:25:21.780
- That's not a problem.
- Okay.

347
00:25:22.030 --> 00:25:23.850
I'll see you after school.

348
00:25:24.610 --> 00:25:25.480
Okay.

349
00:25:28.740 --> 00:25:29.580
Landon Carter

350
00:25:29.740 --> 00:25:30.940
is coming here?

351
00:25:31.370 --> 00:25:34.710
Boy's dangerous, he's careless.
He's the worst kind of bully.

352
00:25:34.870 --> 00:25:36.750
Daddy, what about forgiveness?

353
00:25:38.210 --> 00:25:40.120
I thought we had discussed

354
00:25:40.290 --> 00:25:43.170
that I was going to decide
how I wanted to spend my time

355
00:25:43.340 --> 00:25:44.620
and my life.

356
00:25:44.840 --> 00:25:46.720
It's him I don't trust,
not you.

357
00:25:56.770 --> 00:25:57.720
Hey.

358
00:25:57.940 --> 00:25:58.800
Hi.

359
00:26:00.770 --> 00:26:03.350
You going to keep me out here
all afternoon or what?

360
00:26:04.020 --> 00:26:04.890
Come on in.

361
00:26:10.200 --> 00:26:12.870
My script is in my room,
so I'll be right down.

362
00:26:13.620 --> 00:26:15.910
- Make yourself at home.
- Yeah.

363
00:26:17.660 --> 00:26:18.780
It's not likely.

364
00:26:38.470 --> 00:26:40.300
That is one scary old...

365
00:26:40.680 --> 00:26:43.140
- Jesus!
- No, Jamie's father.

366
00:26:44.560 --> 00:26:45.480
Hello, Mr. Carter.

367
00:26:45.650 --> 00:26:49.060
I understand you won the lead
in the school play. Congratulations.

368
00:26:50.610 --> 00:26:53.530
Thanks for letting me run come over
and run lines with Jamie.

369
00:26:53.690 --> 00:26:54.640
I didn't let you.

370
00:26:56.610 --> 00:26:58.070
It's a school night.

371
00:26:58.530 --> 00:27:00.610
Let's got one thing
straight, Mr. Carter.

372
00:27:02.200 --> 00:27:04.250
You think that on Sundays

373
00:27:04.580 --> 00:27:06.240
I don't see you
from where I stand.

374
00:27:08.790 --> 00:27:09.990
But I see you.

375
00:27:13.590 --> 00:27:15.800
I'll be in my office,
just here.

376
00:27:17.050 --> 00:27:17.910
Ready?

377
00:27:19.760 --> 00:27:20.870
Yeah, let's go.

378
00:27:27.270 --> 00:27:29.670
Landon! Where've you been?

379
00:27:29.850 --> 00:27:31.020
Nowhere.

380
00:27:31.190 --> 00:27:33.430
- Come here.
- What's up?

381
00:27:34.270 --> 00:27:36.430
- Are we cool?
- Yeah, sure.

382
00:27:56.830 --> 00:27:57.870
What the hell?

383
00:28:13.520 --> 00:28:14.770
What are you doing here?

384
00:28:14.930 --> 00:28:16.890
I should ask you
the same question.

385
00:28:17.060 --> 00:28:19.860
Do you normally walk alone
in the cemetery at night?

386
00:28:21.110 --> 00:28:22.060
Maybe.

387
00:28:23.020 --> 00:28:23.780
Where you going?

388
00:28:26.240 --> 00:28:27.350
Come and see.

389
00:28:34.200 --> 00:28:34.870
Okay.

390
00:28:35.450 --> 00:28:36.620
What is that?

391
00:28:37.500 --> 00:28:41.030
This is my telescope.
I built it when I was twelve.

392
00:28:43.040 --> 00:28:43.960
Take a look.

393
00:28:49.840 --> 00:28:50.670
Saturn.

394
00:28:51.840 --> 00:28:53.750
- Very cool.
- Yeah.

395
00:28:54.550 --> 00:28:58.470
I'm planning on building a larger one
so I can see the Comet Hyakutake.

396
00:28:58.770 --> 00:29:01.800
It comes this spring, but nobody
knows when it's coming back.

397
00:29:01.980 --> 00:29:03.560
Ah, nature's miracles.

398
00:29:05.400 --> 00:29:06.400
I get it.

399
00:29:06.650 --> 00:29:07.680
Get what?

400
00:29:07.860 --> 00:29:09.600
That you're into all this stuff.

401
00:29:11.230 --> 00:29:12.820
This stuff?

402
00:29:13.610 --> 00:29:15.160
I have my beliefs.

403
00:29:15.910 --> 00:29:16.690
I have faith,

404
00:29:16.860 --> 00:29:17.780
but don't you?

405
00:29:17.950 --> 00:29:18.810
No,

406
00:29:19.410 --> 00:29:21.620
there's too much bad shit
in this world.

407
00:29:21.790 --> 00:29:23.690
Without suffering
there'd be no compassion.

408
00:29:24.080 --> 00:29:26.070
Tell that to those who suffer.

409
00:29:30.590 --> 00:29:32.240
This is what I love
about early spring.

410
00:29:32.420 --> 00:29:34.800
Where've those legs
been hiding all winter?

411
00:29:34.960 --> 00:29:36.000
She's trashy.

412
00:29:36.340 --> 00:29:39.840
- Well, if it isn't the Virgin Mary.
- Dude, here comes your leading lady.

413
00:29:41.050 --> 00:29:41.890
Hey, Carter.

414
00:29:42.890 --> 00:29:43.750
So I'll see you after school?

415
00:29:46.520 --> 00:29:47.890
In your dreams.

416
00:29:58.240 --> 00:30:00.900
Hi! Where's your sweater?

417
00:30:08.910 --> 00:30:09.910
Let's get out of here.

418
00:30:41.230 --> 00:30:42.430
Come on, Jamie.

419
00:30:43.360 --> 00:30:45.150
Open the door, please!

420
00:30:47.990 --> 00:30:49.070
What do you want?

421
00:30:50.200 --> 00:30:51.700
You're not in a good mood.

422
00:30:52.660 --> 00:30:53.910
You don't miss a thing.

423
00:30:54.370 --> 00:30:56.940
I was hoping
we could run lines together.

424
00:30:58.410 --> 00:31:01.420
Okay, but just
not so anyone knows, right?

425
00:31:02.040 --> 00:31:05.000
I just figured we could surprise
everyone with how good I get.

426
00:31:06.550 --> 00:31:08.340
We could be secret friends.

427
00:31:08.720 --> 00:31:09.830
Exactly!

428
00:31:10.090 --> 00:31:12.250
It's like you're reading
my mind!

429
00:31:12.640 --> 00:31:14.710
Great.
Maybe you could read mine?

430
00:31:20.560 --> 00:31:21.680
Jamie,

431
00:31:21.850 --> 00:31:23.350
- I can't just be your friend.
- Landon,

432
00:31:23.730 --> 00:31:26.110
look, I thought
I saw something in you.

433
00:31:27.320 --> 00:31:28.570
Something good.

434
00:31:29.150 --> 00:31:30.430
But I was very wrong.

435
00:31:37.870 --> 00:31:38.980
Damn it!

436
00:31:44.250 --> 00:31:46.160
Sorry.

437
00:32:06.350 --> 00:32:09.770
Jamie Sullivan Red Cross.
Stars and Planets.

438
00:32:09.940 --> 00:32:12.430
Drama Club. Ambition:
To witness a miracle.

439
00:32:23.870 --> 00:32:25.240
You know the answer?

440
00:32:27.540 --> 00:32:28.790
Look, I know you know.

441
00:32:37.300 --> 00:32:40.500
Okay, it's you, me,
and the basket.

442
00:32:40.970 --> 00:32:43.370
We form the three corners
of a triangle.

443
00:32:43.720 --> 00:32:45.430
Take a step towards the basket.

444
00:32:48.930 --> 00:32:51.560
Now am I at the same angle to you
and the basket as before?

445
00:32:52.640 --> 00:32:54.270
- Yeah.
- Are you?

446
00:32:54.770 --> 00:32:55.470
Yeah.

447
00:32:56.060 --> 00:32:57.650
So what did we just make?

448
00:33:01.070 --> 00:33:02.230
A similar triangle?

449
00:33:03.070 --> 00:33:03.850
Yes!

450
00:33:04.280 --> 00:33:05.860
Okay, make me an isosceles.

451
00:33:07.820 --> 00:33:09.900
You got it, two sides the same.

452
00:33:11.280 --> 00:33:12.540
Enough of this, let's play.

453
00:35:24.700 --> 00:35:26.490
I came to say I'm sorry.

454
00:35:29.950 --> 00:35:31.200
Well, you did.

455
00:35:32.120 --> 00:35:33.240
Feel better?

456
00:35:34.040 --> 00:35:36.000
No. I feel like shit.

457
00:35:36.540 --> 00:35:37.570
You know what?

458
00:35:37.880 --> 00:35:40.250
I actually thought
I wanted to be your friend.

459
00:35:44.420 --> 00:35:46.330
And now I have no idea why.

460
00:35:46.840 --> 00:35:47.840
No idea.

461
00:35:51.890 --> 00:35:53.600
I made that jump once.

462
00:35:54.140 --> 00:35:55.880
I thought I was a badass.

463
00:35:57.850 --> 00:36:01.940
I remember actually saying
that I meant to belly-flop.

464
00:36:05.780 --> 00:36:06.860
Did it hurt?

465
00:36:09.990 --> 00:36:11.020
Like hell.

466
00:36:13.030 --> 00:36:13.950
Good.

467
00:36:22.920 --> 00:36:24.880
So I guess I'll see you
at school then.

468
00:36:30.630 --> 00:36:33.470
- Pour me a drink, Joey.
- You promised me, Tommy.

469
00:36:33.760 --> 00:36:36.300
No more
of your no-goodnik schemes!

470
00:36:37.760 --> 00:36:39.420
You promised me we'd go to Paris.

471
00:36:39.600 --> 00:36:41.020
I'm not going to
sit on my keister

472
00:36:41.180 --> 00:36:44.140
and watch all the fat cats
get rich. Trust me.

473
00:36:44.980 --> 00:36:46.060
This is a sure thing.

474
00:36:46.730 --> 00:36:47.430
That's it!

475
00:36:48.610 --> 00:36:49.550
We are through!

476
00:36:50.020 --> 00:36:52.780
Go ahead and run your booze,
you big dope!

477
00:36:53.030 --> 00:36:54.530
And I hope you drown in it!

478
00:36:55.780 --> 00:36:56.700
So!

479
00:36:57.610 --> 00:36:59.490
You must be
the new girl he's hired.

480
00:37:00.120 --> 00:37:01.200
The singer?

481
00:37:02.700 --> 00:37:04.940
You want some free advice
about this one?

482
00:37:06.200 --> 00:37:08.160
Stay far away.
He's nothing but

483
00:37:08.330 --> 00:37:10.160
trouble in cheap spats.

484
00:37:13.920 --> 00:37:15.460
Look, I ain't blaming you.

485
00:37:17.050 --> 00:37:19.120
I ain't asking
for forgiveness, either.

486
00:37:20.970 --> 00:37:22.630
ljust did what I had to.

487
00:37:28.520 --> 00:37:30.060
When you walked out

488
00:37:31.060 --> 00:37:33.390
of the rain
and into my club,

489
00:37:34.690 --> 00:37:36.930
that wasn't just
a coincidence, was it?

490
00:37:37.320 --> 00:37:38.690
Nothing's coincidence.

491
00:37:39.860 --> 00:37:40.890
Your face...

492
00:37:42.530 --> 00:37:44.320
You look so familiar.

493
00:37:44.740 --> 00:37:47.120
Like this dame I knew once,

494
00:37:47.490 --> 00:37:49.200
only it wasn't real,
it was a dream.

495
00:37:49.490 --> 00:37:51.650
Tell me about this dream girl.

496
00:37:57.080 --> 00:37:58.090
Well, I don't...

497
00:37:58.840 --> 00:37:59.920
remember.

498
00:38:04.880 --> 00:38:05.970
All I know...

499
00:38:10.760 --> 00:38:12.010
is you're beautiful.

500
00:38:22.770 --> 00:38:24.190
The song, the song!

501
00:38:24.820 --> 00:38:25.930
The dream.

502
00:38:28.320 --> 00:38:29.270
Help me to remember.

503
00:38:31.990 --> 00:38:33.270
Will you sing for me?

504
00:38:39.620 --> 00:38:42.790
There's a song that's inside

505
00:38:43.170 --> 00:38:45.330
of my soul

506
00:38:48.760 --> 00:38:52.930
It's the one
that I've tried to write

507
00:38:53.180 --> 00:38:56.140
over and over again

508
00:38:57.510 --> 00:39:02.340
I will wake in the infinite cold

509
00:39:06.610 --> 00:39:09.520
But you sing to me over

510
00:39:09.980 --> 00:39:13.490
and over and over again

511
00:39:14.280 --> 00:39:16.740
So I lay

512
00:39:16.910 --> 00:39:21.030
my head back down

513
00:39:23.200 --> 00:39:27.250
