552
00:42:51.770 --> 00:42:54.140
- Great, honey.
- Thank you, but please stop.

553
00:42:54.310 --> 00:42:56.770
- Don't be home too late.
- Okay. Thank you.

554
00:42:56.940 --> 00:42:58.400
Okay, okay.

555
00:43:00.150 --> 00:43:03.650
- Interesting rewrite you did out there.
- I did my best.

556
00:43:03.940 --> 00:43:05.820
Your acting didn't suck either.

557
00:43:06.740 --> 00:43:08.980
- Got to go. Take it easy, man.
- Okay.

558
00:43:10.320 --> 00:43:11.610
Landon, you were marvelous!

559
00:43:12.080 --> 00:43:12.940
Thank you.

560
00:43:17.870 --> 00:43:18.570
Landon?

561
00:43:19.250 --> 00:43:20.530
Fine performance.

562
00:43:20.710 --> 00:43:22.420
- What're you doing here?
- I thought

563
00:43:22.590 --> 00:43:24.660
we'd get a bite.

564
00:43:24.840 --> 00:43:25.700
I'm not hungry.

565
00:43:25.920 --> 00:43:28.470
- Landon, don't walk away.
- You taught me how.

566
00:43:37.810 --> 00:43:39.090
Oh, my God.

567
00:43:40.480 --> 00:43:41.850
Look who's here.

568
00:43:47.270 --> 00:43:48.780
Don't look at him.

569
00:43:49.030 --> 00:43:50.650
You don't want to stare too much.

570
00:43:53.860 --> 00:43:56.110
I guess he doesn't want
to sit with us.

571
00:44:10.550 --> 00:44:13.720
- People can see.
- And that would ruin your reputation?

572
00:44:14.550 --> 00:44:15.670
What's that?

573
00:44:17.340 --> 00:44:21.180
I'm reading all the books on Rothman's
list of contemporary American authors.

574
00:44:22.350 --> 00:44:24.420
And how many books are there?

575
00:44:25.230 --> 00:44:26.310
A hundred.

576
00:44:27.310 --> 00:44:30.560
But then there are his British list
and his European list.

577
00:44:32.230 --> 00:44:35.030
So is this on your list,
to read all these books?

578
00:44:43.120 --> 00:44:45.910
Jamie, I'm trying here, okay?

579
00:44:47.500 --> 00:44:48.500
Maybe...

580
00:44:50.620 --> 00:44:52.450
Maybe I miss spending
time with you.

581
00:44:54.750 --> 00:44:56.410
Maybe you inspire me.

582
00:44:57.880 --> 00:44:59.130
Sounds like bull.

583
00:44:59.590 --> 00:45:01.130
- Which part?
- All of it.

584
00:45:01.470 --> 00:45:03.510
- It's not.
- Prove it.

585
00:45:12.600 --> 00:45:13.380
Jamie!

586
00:45:15.730 --> 00:45:18.270
You don't know
how to be a friend.

587
00:45:18.440 --> 00:45:20.350
- I don't want to just be your friend.
- You don't know what you want.

588
00:45:20.530 --> 00:45:23.640
Neither do you. You're scared
someone wants to be with you.

589
00:45:23.820 --> 00:45:27.320
- Why would that scare me?
- You couldn't hide behind your books,

590
00:45:27.530 --> 00:45:29.080
or your telescope...

591
00:45:29.870 --> 00:45:31.940
or your faith.

592
00:45:32.120 --> 00:45:34.410
You know the real reason
why you're scared?

593
00:45:35.710 --> 00:45:37.580
You want to be with me too.

594
00:45:59.060 --> 00:46:02.020
We're going to get
this party jumping!

595
00:46:02.440 --> 00:46:06.140
Can you turn down Soul Train?
Some of us are trying to work.

596
00:46:06.320 --> 00:46:09.520
You really know
how to bust a robot's groove.

597
00:46:10.110 --> 00:46:12.410
But it's all good
because Club Landon

598
00:46:12.570 --> 00:46:15.410
and Club Eric is jumping now.
What we got here?

599
00:46:17.790 --> 00:46:18.980
Okay, okay,

600
00:46:19.160 --> 00:46:22.920
