but what the hell is this?

601
00:46:23.250 --> 00:46:24.830
Jamie lent it to me.

602
00:46:26.380 --> 00:46:28.540
Now she's got you listening to
her people's music.

603
00:46:28.750 --> 00:46:30.340
Her people?

604
00:46:30.510 --> 00:46:35.080
Yeah, Bible-hugging-crucifix-wearing-

605
00:46:35.260 --> 00:46:37.750
honk-if-you-love-Jesus people.

606
00:46:38.180 --> 00:46:39.510
- She's not like that.
- Well...

607
00:46:40.060 --> 00:46:41.560
You know, you got...

608
00:46:41.970 --> 00:46:46.100
Belinda thinking that little lip action
between you and Jamie was kind of real.

609
00:46:54.070 --> 00:46:58.020
What's with you? You don't have time
for your real friends anymore.

610
00:46:58.860 --> 00:47:00.030
I don't know, buddy.

611
00:47:00.740 --> 00:47:01.860
I'm just over it.

612
00:47:03.240 --> 00:47:05.910
I'm sick and tired of doing
the same old shit all the time.

613
00:47:07.000 --> 00:47:10.080
This girl's changed you
and you don't even know it, man.

614
00:47:11.420 --> 00:47:13.880
- Belinda say that, too?
- No.

615
00:47:15.630 --> 00:47:16.710
I did.

616
00:47:28.470 --> 00:47:29.140
You.

617
00:47:30.430 --> 00:47:31.550
Me.

618
00:47:37.360 --> 00:47:38.730
What is it?

619
00:47:39.360 --> 00:47:40.780
I got you something.

620
00:47:45.200 --> 00:47:46.370
Thank you.

621
00:47:50.370 --> 00:47:52.500
I'll see you at school.

622
00:47:53.960 --> 00:47:54.900
Okay.

623
00:48:04.380 --> 00:48:05.250
Mr. Carter.

624
00:48:06.180 --> 00:48:07.340
Later, Reverend.

625
00:48:23.480 --> 00:48:24.230
Jamie.

626
00:48:30.660 --> 00:48:32.160
Boys like that...

627
00:48:34.700 --> 00:48:35.570
They have...

628
00:48:41.250 --> 00:48:42.500
They have expectations.

629
00:48:44.170 --> 00:48:46.800
The rules around here
aren't going to change.

630
00:48:47.960 --> 00:48:49.050
Fine.

631
00:48:53.970 --> 00:48:56.680
You might not care
what I say or think,

632
00:48:56.850 --> 00:48:58.670
but you should care
about God's opinion.

633
00:49:00.970 --> 00:49:03.600
I think He wants me to be happy.

634
00:49:06.980 --> 00:49:08.640
It's just a sweater.

635
00:49:10.780 --> 00:49:12.990
I'm going to make us dinner.

636
00:49:25.120 --> 00:49:26.860
I talked to your dad today.

637
00:49:27.830 --> 00:49:31.120
Said he say you at the play
for about ten seconds.

638
00:49:31.500 --> 00:49:32.420
Yeah.

639
00:49:33.000 --> 00:49:36.200
Sending a check once a month
doesn't exactly make him your father.

640
00:49:39.300 --> 00:49:41.260
Landon, there are a lot of reasons--

641
00:49:41.930 --> 00:49:43.130
He left us.

642
00:49:45.180 --> 00:49:46.640
You need to forgive him, too.

643
00:49:53.020 --> 00:49:54.680
Jamie Sullivan!

644
00:49:55.110 --> 00:49:57.680
Oh me, oh my,
look at Jamie Sullivan.

645
00:49:57.860 --> 00:49:59.900
She was looking all right
in that play.

646
00:50:01.780 --> 00:50:03.060
She does not look hot.

647
00:50:03.240 --> 00:50:06.520
I would have to say
during the play, she looked...

648
00:50:06.950 --> 00:50:10.570
- She looked hot.
- I have the best idea.

649
00:50:11.710 --> 00:50:14.000
Can you do something,
like move it?

650
00:50:15.540 --> 00:50:17.420
Move it around a little
something here.

651
00:50:18.500 --> 00:50:19.700
Take one.

652
00:50:21.340 --> 00:50:22.590
That's it.

653
00:50:24.010 --> 00:50:26.300
Let me stop it for a second.
Check it out.

654
00:50:29.640 --> 00:50:31.060
Hey, look at this.

655
00:50:34.770 --> 00:50:35.470
Take one.

656
00:50:36.770 --> 00:50:37.380
Look.

657
00:50:42.150 --> 00:50:43.150
Jamie.

658
00:50:43.610 --> 00:50:45.110
- Hi.
- Hi.

659
00:50:45.690 --> 00:50:49.150
I just want you to no know,
no hard feelings.

660
00:50:50.280 --> 00:50:52.580
Landon and I are way over.

661
00:50:53.660 --> 00:50:56.200
I really don't know
what you're talking about.

662
00:50:58.620 --> 00:50:59.570
Jamie.

663
00:51:01.040 --> 00:51:02.830
You'd be so beautiful

664
00:51:03.500 --> 00:51:05.300
if you knew
how to do your make-up.

665
00:51:08.630 --> 00:51:10.130
Come on, eat lunch with me.

666
00:51:11.220 --> 00:51:12.870
- Want a Tic Tac?
- No, thanks.

667
00:51:13.050 --> 00:51:13.920
Okay.

668
00:51:28.770 --> 00:51:29.890
Is that you?

669
00:51:36.530 --> 00:51:37.700
Nice bod.

670
00:52:06.980 --> 00:52:07.730
Look.

671
00:52:08.310 --> 00:52:10.690
This is about me, okay,
this is not you.

672
00:52:12.020 --> 00:52:12.770
Stay here.

673
00:52:17.740 --> 00:52:20.740
Hey, man, no wonder
you been keeping her locked up.

674
00:52:20.950 --> 00:52:23.520
I had no idea
this was underneath all that.

675
00:52:26.660 --> 00:52:28.950
- Dean, stop it!
- You stay out of this!

676
00:52:37.540 --> 00:52:39.250
- We're through.
- That's great.

677
00:52:39.420 --> 00:52:40.590
We're through.

678
00:52:41.210 --> 00:52:42.760
We are through forever!

679
00:52:42.920 --> 00:52:44.470
- You okay?
- You made a mistake, Landon!

680
00:52:44.630 --> 00:52:45.750
Sure?

681
00:52:46.140 --> 00:52:47.760
Let's get the hell out of here.

682
00:52:49.510 --> 00:52:50.550
You chickenshit!

683
00:52:52.930 --> 00:52:54.440
Baby, I'm sorry.

684
00:52:55.100 --> 00:52:57.560
Okay?
They're animals, all right?

685
00:52:59.650 --> 00:53:01.070
Want me to take you home?

686
00:53:03.990 --> 00:53:05.180
Let's get out of here.

687
00:53:07.110 --> 00:53:08.770
Are you sure you're okay?

688
00:53:09.870 --> 00:53:10.980
I'm fine.

689
00:53:12.910 --> 00:53:14.290
But thank you for everything.

690
00:53:14.580 --> 00:53:15.780
You're welcome.

691
00:53:23.040 --> 00:53:24.790
I want to ask you something.

692
00:53:25.590 --> 00:53:26.510
Okay.

693
00:53:31.840 --> 00:53:34.880
Will you go out with me
on Saturday night?

694
00:53:39.140 --> 00:53:40.940
I'm sorry. I can't go.

695
00:53:45.610 --> 00:53:48.720
- You got something else going on?
- No.

696
00:53:49.190 --> 00:53:50.390
It's not that.

697
00:53:51.740 --> 00:53:52.900
Then what is it?

698
00:53:59.790 --> 00:54:01.410
I'm not allowed to date.

699
00:54:06.540 --> 00:54:07.960
Do not be deceived.

700
00:54:08.290 --> 00:54:10.120
God is not mocked...

701
00:54:13.090 --> 00:54:16.840
Whatever a man sows,
that he shall also reap.

702
00:54:18.140 --> 00:54:19.850
For he who sows to his flesh,

703
00:54:20.510 --> 00:54:22.060
will of the flesh reap--

704
00:54:22.850 --> 00:54:23.710
Can I help you?

705
00:54:24.020 --> 00:54:25.210
Yes, sir.

706
00:54:26.310 --> 00:54:29.760
I'd like to ask your daughter out
to dinner on Saturday night.

707
00:54:30.190 --> 00:54:31.270
That's not possible.

708
00:54:34.900 --> 00:54:36.690
With all due respect, sir...

709
00:54:37.150 --> 00:54:38.740
I ask you to reconsider.

710
00:54:40.410 --> 00:54:43.660
With all due respect, Mr. Carter,
I made my decision.

711
00:54:46.790 --> 00:54:49.900
You can exit
the way you entered.

712
00:54:55.540 --> 00:54:58.210
Listen, I'm sorry I haven't treated
Jamie the way I should have.

713
00:54:59.260 --> 00:55:00.880
She deserves more than that.

714
00:55:02.840 --> 00:55:06.510
I'm just asking you
for the same thing you teach us

715
00:55:06.680 --> 00:55:07.510
everyday in church.

716
00:55:10.600 --> 00:55:11.850
And that is faith.

717
00:55:19.860 --> 00:55:21.930
I can't believe you asked
my father's permission.

718
00:55:22.110 --> 00:55:24.320
It's no big deal.
He was cool about it.

719
00:55:25.240 --> 00:55:26.020
Thank you.

720
00:55:26.240 --> 00:55:28.230
- This is for you.
- Thank you very much.

721
00:55:28.870 --> 00:55:30.860
Would you like
something to drink?

722
00:55:31.160 --> 00:55:32.080
Sweet tea, please.

723
00:55:32.410 --> 00:55:33.870
- Make that two.
- Right away.

724
00:55:37.790 --> 00:55:40.910
This restaurant is really nice,
are you sure this is okay?

725
00:55:41.290 --> 00:55:44.050
- Don't even worry about it, okay?
- Okay.

726
00:55:44.210 --> 00:55:45.710
Choose whatever you want.

727
00:55:47.340 --> 00:55:49.580
So, what will it be?

728
00:55:50.930 --> 00:55:52.010
Is everything okay?

729
00:55:53.760 --> 00:55:56.090
- Thank you very much.
- Yeah, me too, thanks.

730
00:56:03.980 --> 00:56:05.360
Would you like to dance?

731
00:56:08.190 --> 00:56:10.570
Sorry, I don't dance.

732
00:56:11.450 --> 00:56:14.900
Me neither. I mean,
not usually in front of anybody.

733
00:56:15.410 --> 00:56:18.290
Well, no. I mean,
I don't...

734
00:56:18.490 --> 00:56:20.450
at all, as in, I can't.

735
00:56:21.710 --> 00:56:23.170
Everybody can dance.

736
00:56:24.620 --> 00:56:26.370
Come on, you can't be that bad.

737
00:56:28.500 --> 00:56:29.500
Please?

738
00:56:30.960 --> 00:56:32.000
For me?

739
00:56:34.130 --> 00:56:35.080
Come on.

740
00:56:50.270 --> 00:56:51.270
Sorry.

741
00:56:51.730 --> 00:56:53.720
I told you I was bad at this.

742
00:56:54.860 --> 00:56:57.070
But, in all fairness,
you did warn me, right?

743
00:56:57.240 --> 00:56:58.240
That's right.

744
00:57:01.280 --> 00:57:02.370
So...

745
00:57:03.740 --> 00:57:05.950
what's number one on your list?

746
00:57:09.210 --> 00:57:09.960
Okay.

747
00:57:11.710 --> 00:57:13.530
Number one on my list is...

748
00:57:14.040 --> 00:57:15.550
getting out of Beaufort.

749
00:57:17.880 --> 00:57:19.790
I don't think getting out
is going to be a problem.

750
00:57:20.760 --> 00:57:23.960
It's more like figuring out
what do to when you get somewhere.

751
00:57:25.220 --> 00:57:26.600
What do you mean?

752
00:57:29.430 --> 00:57:31.420
I mean, you can do anything.

753
00:57:49.370 --> 00:57:52.120
- Where are we going?
- Just hold on, you'll see.

754
00:57:57.210 --> 00:57:59.880
Come on, come on.
Let's go!

755
00:58:00.290 --> 00:58:02.200
- What are we doing?
- Run!

756
00:58:03.260 --> 00:58:05.880
Okay, okay.
Stand there.

757
00:58:06.050 --> 00:58:07.630
- All right.
- One foot there

758
00:58:08.050 --> 00:58:09.760
and one foot here.
- Okay.

759
00:58:12.890 --> 00:58:15.640
You're acting like a crazy person.
What's going on?

760
00:58:15.850 --> 00:58:19.020
Right now,
you're straddling the state line.

761
00:58:21.020 --> 00:58:22.020
Okay.

762
00:58:25.230 --> 00:58:27.310
You're in two places at once.

763
00:58:39.080 --> 00:58:39.750
Okay.

764
00:58:40.460 --> 00:58:43.460
Butterfly, rosebud or star?

765
00:58:44.830 --> 00:58:45.620
You choose.

766
00:58:48.880 --> 00:58:49.660
Butterfly.

767
00:58:49.840 --> 00:58:50.840
Okay.

768
00:58:52.800 --> 00:58:53.670
So...

769
00:58:56.600 --> 00:58:57.790
Where do you want it?

770
00:59:01.930 --> 00:59:03.020
Right here.

771
00:59:11.570 --> 00:59:12.400
Okay.

772
01:00:20.130 --> 01:00:22.510
How can you see
places like this...

773
01:00:24.720 --> 01:00:27.830
and have moments like this,
and not believe?

774
01:00:31.060 --> 01:00:32.880
You're lucky to be so sure.

775
01:00:38.020 --> 01:00:39.440
It's like the wind.

776
01:00:40.730 --> 01:00:44.180
I can't see it, but I feel it.

777
01:00:45.820 --> 01:00:46.900
What do you feel?

778
01:00:50.860 --> 01:00:52.520
I feel wonder

779
01:00:53.700 --> 01:00:54.480
and beauty

780
01:00:55.620 --> 01:00:56.730
joy,

781
01:00:57.500 --> 01:00:58.530
love...

782
01:01:00.620 --> 01:01:03.200
It's the center of everything.

783
01:01:08.170 --> 01:01:09.630
I might kiss you.

784
01:01:12.590 --> 01:01:14.330
I might be bad at it.

785
01:01:18.430 --> 01:01:19.710
That's not possible.

786
01:01:35.280 --> 01:01:36.280
Jamie...

787
01:01:45.000 --> 01:01:46.500
I love you.

788
01:02:00.220 --> 01:02:01.300
Now...

789
01:02:01.800 --> 01:02:04.050
would be the time
to say something.

790
01:02:07.310 --> 01:02:09.630
I told you not to fall
in love with me.

791
01:03:18.040 --> 01:03:18.990
Jamie!

792
01:03:19.580 --> 01:03:21.240
Say good night to Mr. Carter.

793
01:03:23.960 --> 01:03:26.340
Landon, go home.
The night's over.

794
01:03:27.300 --> 01:03:28.800
- Good night.
- Good night.

795
01:03:29.130 --> 01:03:30.300
Good night, sir.

796
01:03:34.600 --> 01:03:36.750
Jamie, your behavior's sinful.

797
01:03:38.140 --> 01:03:39.010
You...

798
01:03:39.270 --> 01:03:41.810
- You act with that boy like you're--
- In love?

799
01:03:44.060 --> 01:03:45.610
Jamie, you are a child.

800
01:03:45.980 --> 01:03:46.820
Dad,

801
01:03:48.150 --> 01:03:49.810
look at me. I'm not a child.

802
01:03:49.980 --> 01:03:51.730
Then stop acting childish!

803
01:03:55.870 --> 01:03:57.060
I love him.

804
01:04:00.580 --> 01:04:04.000
Then be fair to him, Jamie,
before things get worse.

805
01:04:26.390 --> 01:04:27.730
- Hi.
- Hi.

806
01:04:31.060 --> 01:04:32.770
- Will you help me?
- Yeah.

807
01:04:34.190 --> 01:04:36.490
So, what did you tell your father?

808
01:04:37.280 --> 01:04:40.070
The truth,
I just left you out of it.

809
01:04:42.320 --> 01:04:43.780
What do you want to see?

810
01:04:45.740 --> 01:04:46.740
Pluto.

811
01:04:47.240 --> 01:04:50.280
Pluto only rises
a few minutes before the sun.

812
01:04:50.910 --> 01:04:52.540
Right, and...

813
01:04:53.790 --> 01:04:54.880
I have brought us...

814
01:04:55.420 --> 01:04:57.800
a thermos of hot coffee...

815
01:04:58.840 --> 01:04:59.950
and...

816
01:05:00.590 --> 01:05:01.590
a blanket.

817
01:05:03.050 --> 01:05:06.250
- You planned this.
- Oh, I hoped for it.

818
01:05:09.390 --> 01:05:10.850
Are you trying to seduce me?

819
01:05:11.270 --> 01:05:13.510
Why, are you seducible?

820
01:05:16.600 --> 01:05:18.760
That's what I thought, ergo...

821
01:05:19.270 --> 01:05:22.190
a second blanket.

822
01:05:22.940 --> 01:05:24.570
One for me and one for you.

823
01:05:25.030 --> 01:05:25.860
Thank you.

824
01:05:38.870 --> 01:05:41.340
Can you find this star here?

825
01:05:41.960 --> 01:05:42.660
Sure.

826
01:05:53.930 --> 01:05:56.680
So why am I looking for this star?

827
01:05:58.520 --> 01:06:00.480
Because I had it named for you.

828
01:06:03.310 --> 01:06:04.400
See?

829
01:06:05.770 --> 01:06:06.690
It's official.

830
01:06:08.280 --> 01:06:12.060
It's from the International
Star Registry.

831
01:06:16.280 --> 01:06:17.530
This is wonderful!

832
01:06:23.410 --> 01:06:24.500
I love you.

833
01:06:38.470 --> 01:06:40.260
Okay, okay, I'm sorry.

834
01:06:40.970 --> 01:06:42.060
I'm stopping.

835
01:06:51.190 --> 01:06:53.940
So, what's your number one?

836
01:06:59.070 --> 01:07:01.650
To marry in the church
where my mother grew up.

837
01:07:03.030 --> 01:07:04.940
That's where my parents
were married.

838
01:07:35.190 --> 01:07:37.350
- Did you just get in?
- Yeah.

839
01:07:39.530 --> 01:07:42.360
Thank heavens I didn't know,
I would've been panicked.

840
01:07:42.530 --> 01:07:43.640
Sorry.

841
01:07:45.110 --> 01:07:46.110
Landon?

842
01:07:47.240 --> 01:07:48.570
Were you with Jamie?

843
01:07:49.580 --> 01:07:52.860
Landon, be careful,
she's the Reverend's daughter.

844
01:07:53.040 --> 01:07:54.410
- Mom--
- Please!

845
01:07:56.000 --> 01:07:57.660
It's different with her.

846
01:07:58.210 --> 01:07:59.580
It's different with her.

847
01:07:59.920 --> 01:08:00.920
Yes.

848
01:08:03.920 --> 01:08:05.470
It better be
different with her.

849
01:08:09.090 --> 01:08:12.380
I was doing laundry the other day
and I found this.

850
01:08:21.600 --> 01:08:23.480
''Examine a moon rock.

851
01:08:26.320 --> 01:08:27.520
Go to College.

852
01:08:28.820 --> 01:08:30.560
Get into medical school.''

853
01:08:35.620 --> 01:08:36.230
Honey...

854
01:08:38.120 --> 01:08:41.210
These are really
beautiful ambitions.

855
01:08:42.290 --> 01:08:43.160
But...

856
01:08:44.290 --> 01:08:45.790
you're going to have
to work really hard.

857
01:08:46.340 --> 01:08:47.500
I can do that.

858
01:08:51.760 --> 01:08:53.040
Yeah, you can.

859
01:08:58.100 --> 01:08:59.010
Mama...

860
01:09:01.020 --> 01:09:03.730
Jamie has faith in me.

861
01:09:05.600 --> 01:09:06.600
You know?

862
01:09:07.940 --> 01:09:09.560
She makes me want to be...

863
01:09:10.190 --> 01:09:11.220
different.

864
01:09:13.150 --> 01:09:14.100
Better.

865
01:09:16.150 --> 01:09:19.160
I was so drunk,
I don't remember anything.

866
01:09:24.870 --> 01:09:28.070
That's great.
Citizen high to citizen low.

867
01:09:31.130 --> 01:09:34.050
Are you worried
about your college applications?

868
01:09:35.550 --> 01:09:36.300
No.

869
01:09:37.840 --> 01:09:40.380
- I'm not applying to college.
- I thought you said--

870
01:09:40.550 --> 01:09:41.390
No,

871
01:09:41.930 --> 01:09:43.350
you assumed.

872
01:09:43.510 --> 01:09:46.140
Take a year off,
try the Peace Corps?

873
01:09:46.310 --> 01:09:46.920
No.

874
01:09:50.100 --> 01:09:51.350
What are you going to do?

875
01:09:55.940 --> 01:09:57.110
I'm sick.

876
01:09:57.820 --> 01:10:00.570
- I'll take you home, you'll be better--
- No, Landon!

877
01:10:02.570 --> 01:10:03.600
I'm sick.

878
01:10:07.870 --> 01:10:09.150
I have leukemia.

879
01:10:15.960 --> 01:10:16.880
No.

880
01:10:18.290 --> 01:10:20.960
- You're eighteen, you're perfect.
- No,

881
01:10:21.210 --> 01:10:24.970
I found out two years ago.
I've stopped responding to treatments.

882
01:10:30.850 --> 01:10:32.430
So why didn't you tell me?

883
01:10:33.140 --> 01:10:36.140
The doctor said I should go on
and live life normally,

884
01:10:36.310 --> 01:10:38.300
as best I could.

885
01:10:38.900 --> 01:10:41.140
I didn't want anyone
to be weird around me.

886
01:10:41.310 --> 01:10:43.610
- Including me?
- Especially you!

887
01:10:47.860 --> 01:10:50.740
I was getting along fine.
I accepted it,

888
01:10:51.200 --> 01:10:52.620
and then you happened!

889
01:10:57.040 --> 01:11:00.620
I do not need a reason
to be angry with God.

890
01:12:09.810 --> 01:12:11.400
Dad, open the door!

891
01:12:22.740 --> 01:12:23.820
Landon?

892
01:12:26.120 --> 01:12:27.370
I need your help.

893
01:12:27.910 --> 01:12:31.690
- What's wrong, are you okay?
- It's my girlfriend Jamie, she's...

894
01:12:34.370 --> 01:12:35.630
She's got cancer.

895
01:12:36.580 --> 01:12:39.420
And I need you to come
and see her right now.

896
01:12:39.590 --> 01:12:40.760
Okay. Calm down.

897
01:12:41.460 --> 01:12:42.550
Can you help me or not?

898
01:12:42.720 --> 01:12:45.010
I don't know her case,

899
01:12:45.340 --> 01:12:48.050
I don't know her history.
I'd have to talk to her physician.

900
01:12:48.220 --> 01:12:49.340
I'm a cardiologist.
I can't--

901
01:12:49.760 --> 01:12:51.470
Just forget it.

902
01:12:53.020 --> 01:12:53.880
I knew it.

903
01:12:54.390 --> 01:12:56.470
Would you wait? Landon, wait!

904
01:14:35.650 --> 01:14:37.190
You're mom called me.

905
01:14:39.360 --> 01:14:40.740
Talk to me, man.

906
01:14:41.860 --> 01:14:42.980
About what?

907
01:14:46.370 --> 01:14:47.400
About you...

908
01:14:48.540 --> 01:14:49.570
about Jamie.

909
01:14:53.880 --> 01:14:55.420
What's there to talk about?

910
01:14:58.250 --> 01:15:00.460
She's the best person
I've ever known.

911
01:15:05.550 --> 01:15:06.970
I didn't understand.

912
01:15:13.560 --> 01:15:14.730
It's okay, man.

913
01:15:17.190 --> 01:15:18.270
It's okay.

914
01:15:40.880 --> 01:15:42.620
It's so nice to see you again.

915
01:15:42.920 --> 01:15:44.580
You're welcome.
Watch yourself now.

916
01:15:47.630 --> 01:15:48.660
Landon...

917
01:15:48.920 --> 01:15:50.470
I'm not going anywhere.

918
01:15:51.800 --> 01:15:53.430
Please tell Jamie that.

919
01:16:23.580 --> 01:16:24.960
I'm so sorry.

920
01:16:26.830 --> 01:16:28.710
I really should have
told you sooner.

921
01:16:29.090 --> 01:16:31.130
No, I made you do
too many things--

922
01:16:31.300 --> 01:16:33.540
If anything,
you kept me healthy longer.

923
01:16:43.930 --> 01:16:45.050
Are you scared?

924
01:16:47.350 --> 01:16:48.350
To death.

925
01:16:52.190 --> 01:16:52.860
Lighten up.

926
01:16:54.400 --> 01:16:55.570
It's not funny.

927
01:17:17.710 --> 01:17:19.950
I'm scared of not being with you.

928
01:17:24.510 --> 01:17:26.300
Oh, baby, that'll never happen.

929
01:17:36.980 --> 01:17:38.260
I'll be here.

930
01:17:41.400 --> 01:17:42.320
Mom?

931
01:17:45.320 --> 01:17:46.910
Can you do me a favor?

932
01:19:15.940 --> 01:19:17.110
So...

933
01:19:19.870 --> 01:19:21.240
I talked to Eric.

934
01:19:28.790 --> 01:19:30.210
Need some help with this stuff?

935
01:19:32.040 --> 01:19:32.990
Sure.

936
01:20:11.200 --> 01:20:13.610
Jamie, what's that boy
doing in the yard?

937
01:20:16.960 --> 01:20:18.210
What's the matter?

938
01:20:18.960 --> 01:20:19.830
Jamie, honey.

939
01:21:25.980 --> 01:21:27.010
Landon.

940
01:21:28.360 --> 01:21:29.770
Go on home, son.

941
01:21:30.610 --> 01:21:31.980
I'm not tired.

942
01:21:34.490 --> 01:21:36.780
I need just a minute with her.

943
01:21:45.370 --> 01:21:46.960
I'll be back, okay?

944
01:21:47.250 --> 01:21:48.250
Okay.

945
01:22:12.940 --> 01:22:13.610
Daddy...

946
01:22:16.360 --> 01:22:17.820
so serious.

947
01:22:28.580 --> 01:22:29.910
Do you remember...

948
01:22:30.370 --> 01:22:32.030
when you were about...

949
01:22:32.540 --> 01:22:34.080
five or six...

950
01:22:34.790 --> 01:22:37.030
and you said
you hated gravity...

951
01:22:38.250 --> 01:22:41.210
and you wanted to jump off
the roof and fly?

952
01:22:44.010 --> 01:22:47.790
I was so angry at you
for making me come down.

953
01:22:48.930 --> 01:22:50.890
Honey, if I kept you too close

954
01:22:51.890 --> 01:22:54.100
it's because
I wanted to keep you longer.

955
01:22:55.310 --> 01:22:56.430
Dad...

956
01:23:01.480 --> 01:23:02.510
You know,

957
01:23:02.900 --> 01:23:04.810
when I lost your mother...

958
01:23:10.700 --> 01:23:13.660
I was afraid that my heart
would never open again.

959
01:23:23.000 --> 01:23:25.210
Jamie, I couldn't
look at you for days!

960
01:23:32.050 --> 01:23:33.140
But, then...

961
01:23:38.260 --> 01:23:40.220
I love you so much.

962
01:24:06.870 --> 01:24:08.580
- Hi.
- Hi.

963
01:24:09.130 --> 01:24:10.590
I wanted to give you these.

964
01:24:12.340 --> 01:24:13.880
The pictures from the play.

965
01:24:20.890 --> 01:24:22.390
I'm sorry about the flyers.

966
01:24:22.970 --> 01:24:24.350
Hey, it doesn't matter.

967
01:24:25.680 --> 01:24:26.430
Yeah.

968
01:24:28.440 --> 01:24:30.510
I guess you're
with who you should be.

969
01:24:32.980 --> 01:24:34.400
It's like she chose you.

970
01:24:36.280 --> 01:24:38.400
Yeah, I don't even know why.

971
01:24:42.410 --> 01:24:43.440
I do.

972
01:25:24.360 --> 01:25:25.560
How you feeling?

973
01:25:26.360 --> 01:25:29.110
- I'm okay, how are you?
- Pretty good.

974
01:25:30.160 --> 01:25:32.370
- I have something for you.
- You do?

975
01:25:38.500 --> 01:25:40.240
Don't worry, it's not a Bible.

976
01:25:42.040 --> 01:25:44.030
It was my mother's.
It's got...

977
01:25:45.210 --> 01:25:47.420
quotes from her favorite
books and...

978
01:25:48.840 --> 01:25:50.630
quotes by famous people.

979
01:25:51.380 --> 01:25:52.250
Her thoughts.

980
01:25:54.300 --> 01:25:55.250
Come on.

981
01:25:55.970 --> 01:25:57.390
Okay, let's check it out.

982
01:26:04.310 --> 01:26:05.150
Okay.

983
01:26:06.360 --> 01:26:07.640
''What is a friend?''

984
01:26:08.570 --> 01:26:11.190
''It's a single soul
dwelling in two bodies.''

985
01:26:11.780 --> 01:26:12.980
Aristotle.

986
01:26:14.450 --> 01:26:15.230
Right here.

987
01:26:15.870 --> 01:26:16.730
Okay.

988
01:26:18.530 --> 01:26:20.120
''Find out who you are...

989
01:26:21.330 --> 01:26:22.830
and do it on purpose.''

990
01:26:25.210 --> 01:26:26.240
That's Dolly Parton.

991
01:26:28.590 --> 01:26:30.550
I always thought she was smart.

992
01:26:41.140 --> 01:26:43.850
''Love is always patient and kind,

993
01:26:44.770 --> 01:26:45.800
it is never jealous.

994
01:26:47.810 --> 01:26:50.480
Love is never
boastful or conceited.

995
01:26:52.020 --> 01:26:53.480
It is never rude

996
01:26:53.730 --> 01:26:54.980
or selfish.

997
01:26:55.650 --> 01:26:57.560
It does not take offense...

998
01:26:58.110 --> 01:26:59.700
and is not resentful.''

999
01:27:09.540 --> 01:27:11.080
You know what I figured out today?

1000
01:27:11.580 --> 01:27:12.420
What?

1001
01:27:17.000 --> 01:27:18.460
Maybe God...

1002
01:27:20.470 --> 01:27:22.540
has a bigger plan for me

1003
01:27:23.430 --> 01:27:25.010
than I had for myself.

1004
01:27:26.550 --> 01:27:27.470
Like,

1005
01:27:28.390 --> 01:27:30.430
this journey never ends.

1006
01:27:33.190 --> 01:27:36.440
Like, you were sent to me
because I'm sick...

1007
01:27:40.610 --> 01:27:42.400
to help me through all this.

1008
01:27:54.620 --> 01:27:56.000
You're my angel.

1009
01:28:14.970 --> 01:28:17.930
- What's going on?
- I get to go home.

1010
01:28:18.140 --> 01:28:20.380
Please thank your father for me.

1011
01:28:21.350 --> 01:28:22.440
What does she mean?

1012
01:28:22.600 --> 01:28:24.400
Your father's been trying
to reach you.

1013
01:28:25.320 --> 01:28:28.070
He's going to pay
for private home care.

1014
01:28:58.600 --> 01:28:59.680
Thank you.

1015
01:29:20.490 --> 01:29:21.520
Sorry.

1016
01:29:24.540 --> 01:29:26.000
It's all right.

1017
01:30:03.650 --> 01:30:05.560
I have to finish this tonight.

1018
01:30:06.200 --> 01:30:07.780
Here, something hot.

1019
01:30:11.660 --> 01:30:14.370
I'm almost finished with the rocker.
Did she order the mirrors?

1020
01:30:14.540 --> 01:30:16.330
Yeah, they're in here.

1021
01:30:17.250 --> 01:30:20.920
- What are you using for side bearings?
- An old phonographic turntable.

1022
01:30:21.500 --> 01:30:24.210
Do you think
you'll get it done by tomorrow?

1023
01:30:27.430 --> 01:30:29.640
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1024
01:30:30.930 --> 01:30:32.180
It's beautiful.

1025
01:30:33.220 --> 01:30:35.050
Okay, it's time. Go check it out.

1026
01:30:35.720 --> 01:30:37.230
Okay.

1027
01:31:16.550 --> 01:31:17.720
There it is.

1028
01:31:20.810 --> 01:31:21.920
Come here.

1029
01:31:22.520 --> 01:31:23.770
Come look.

1030
01:31:26.230 --> 01:31:28.050
Come look, quick.

1031
01:31:38.240 --> 01:31:39.740
That is cool.

1032
01:31:50.500 --> 01:31:51.840
Do you love me?

1033
01:31:59.510 --> 01:32:01.420
Will you do something for me, then?

1034
01:32:01.720 --> 01:32:02.800
Anything.

1035
01:32:07.310 --> 01:32:08.730
Will you marry me?

1036
01:33:33.970 --> 01:33:37.720
Love is always
patient and kind.

1037
01:33:38.850 --> 01:33:40.390
It is never jealous.

1038
01:33:40.560 --> 01:33:41.390
I love you.

1039
01:33:41.560 --> 01:33:42.670
It is never boast-full...

1040
01:33:42.850 --> 01:33:43.630
I love you.

1041
01:33:43.810 --> 01:33:45.090
...or conceited.

1042
01:33:45.900 --> 01:33:48.360
It is never rude or selfish.

1043
01:33:48.650 --> 01:33:50.440
It does not take offense

1044
01:33:51.190 --> 01:33:52.990
and is not resentful.

1045
01:33:53.740 --> 01:33:55.700
Love takes no pleasure

1046
01:33:56.160 --> 01:33:58.200
in other peoples' sins...

1047
01:33:58.410 --> 01:34:00.980
but delights in the truth.

1048
01:34:02.410 --> 01:34:04.790
It is always ready to excuse

1049
01:34:05.330 --> 01:34:07.240
to trust, to hope

1050
01:34:08.080 --> 01:34:09.670
and to endure...

1051
01:34:11.960 --> 01:34:13.340
whatever comes.

1052
01:34:14.880 --> 01:34:15.910
I,

1053
01:34:16.510 --> 01:34:17.760
Landon Rollins Carter...

1054
01:34:17.930 --> 01:34:20.390
I, Jamie Elizabeth Sullivan,
do solemnly swear...

1055
01:34:20.550 --> 01:34:23.510
...do solemnly swear to take
Jamie Elizabeth Sullivan...

1056
01:34:23.680 --> 01:34:25.500
...to take
Landon Rollins Carter...

1057
01:34:26.270 --> 01:34:28.560
- ...as my lawfully wedded wife...
- ...as my lawfully wedded husband...

1058
01:34:28.730 --> 01:34:30.630
...to honor and to cherish her...

1059
01:34:30.940 --> 01:34:33.560
- ...all the days of my life.
- ...all the days of my life.

1060
01:34:54.420 --> 01:34:57.530
Jamie and I had
a perfect summer together,

1061
01:34:58.380 --> 01:34:59.630
with more love

1062
01:34:59.880 --> 01:35:02.420
than lots of people know
in a lifetime.

1063
01:35:03.260 --> 01:35:06.840
And then she went
with her unfailing faith.

1064
01:35:30.240 --> 01:35:31.830
It's been four years...

1065
01:35:34.040 --> 01:35:36.870
but the vision of Jamie
walking towards me...

1066
01:35:39.120 --> 01:35:40.860
will stay with me forever.

1067
01:35:43.500 --> 01:35:45.550
Hello, Mr. Carter. Come in.

1068
01:35:53.300 --> 01:35:55.460
- Have a seat, please.
- Thank you.

1069
01:36:03.690 --> 01:36:04.770
Landon.

1070
01:36:09.190 --> 01:36:11.520
- You g look good.
- Thank you. You too.

1071
01:36:12.030 --> 01:36:13.310
I'm getting by.

1072
01:36:25.670 --> 01:36:27.380
What's new, Landon?

1073
01:36:28.000 --> 01:36:30.410
I got into medical school.

1074
01:36:30.590 --> 01:36:32.300
Your mother told me that.

1075
01:36:33.260 --> 01:36:34.590
We're so proud of you.

1076
01:36:36.170 --> 01:36:37.880
Jamie would have been
proud of you too.

1077
01:36:41.220 --> 01:36:42.090
Listen.

1078
01:36:48.850 --> 01:36:50.310
I want you...

1079
01:36:51.520 --> 01:36:52.980
